# ğŸ§  Sabse Pehle Clear Karo â€” DTO kya hota hai?

DTO ka full form hota hai:
Data Transfer Object

Ye normally use hota hai:
* API me data bhejne ke liye
* Ya frontend ko limited data dene ke liye
* Database se direct connected nahi hota

# ğŸ”´ Ab Problem Kahan Hai?

Tumhara `RestaurantDto` aisa likha hai:

@Data
@Embeddable
public class RestaurantDto

âš ï¸ Yaha pe `@Embeddable` laga hua hai.

Iska matlab:

ğŸ‘‰ Ye normal DTO nahi hai
ğŸ‘‰ Ye actually database ke andar embed hone wala component ban gaya hai


# ğŸ“¦ `@Embeddable` ka Simple Matlab

Agar kisi class pe `@Embeddable` lagate ho, toh:

> Us class ka alag table nahi banega
> Uske fields kisi dusri Entity ke table ke andar store honge

Jaise tumhare Restaurant me:

@Embedded
private ContactInformation contactInformation;

Matlab:
ContactInformation ke fields â†’ Restaurant table ke andar hi save honge.


# ğŸ”µ Ab Tumhara Restaurant Entity Samjhte Hain

@Entity
public class Restaurant

Ye kya karta hai?

âœ” Database me table banata hai
âœ” Relations manage karta hai
âœ” Orders, Foods, Address sab handle karta hai

Ye full heavy object hai.

# ğŸŸ¡ Ab Tumhara RestaurantDto

@Embeddable
public class RestaurantDto


Isme sirf:

private String title;
private List<String> images;
private String description;
private Long id;

Ye ek **light version** hai restaurant ka.

Par kyunki tumne `@Embeddable` laga diya hai:

ğŸ‘‰ Ye database ke structure ka part ban gaya hai
ğŸ‘‰ Ye pure DTO jaisa behave nahi kar raha


# ğŸ’¥ Important Difference

## ğŸ”· Restaurant (Entity)

* Database table banata hai
* Relationships rakhta hai
* Full data rakhta hai
* Heavy object

## ğŸ”· RestaurantDto (Normally)

* Sirf API ke liye hota hai
* Database se direct link nahi
* No annotations like `@Entity`, `@Embeddable`, `@Column`
* Sirf simple class


# ğŸ”¥ Short Summary (Exam Style)

| Restaurant Entity   | RestaurantDto      |
| ------------------- | ------------------ |
| Database table      | API data object    |
| Heavy object        | Light object       |
| Has relations       | No relations       |
| Has JPA annotations | No JPA annotations |

